1. Jamal is feeling off lately. He likes his job OK. His relationships and life in general are fine. But he doesn’t feel enthused about anything—including his future. Where on the mental health continuum is Jamal likely to fall at this point in time?
Solution : C. Languishing

2. True or false: When it comes to the mental health continuum, shifting between phases typically takes months, years, or even longer.
Solution : B. False
